The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Discus thrower to leave India
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Discus thrower to leave India
                      
	New Delhi: Olympic-bound discus thrower Harwant Kaur on Sunday said she was shifting her base to Australia because she did not have a good job in India to continue her athletics career.         
	The Punjab-based athletes decision puts a question mark over her participation at next months Beijing Olympics         
	I am shifting base to Australia because I dont even have a good job in India and I may represent Australia in international competitions, she told a news channel.         
	Harwant alleged that she was not given a promotion by the Punjab Police and instead demoted to the rank of constable from Assistant sub-inspector, the news channel reported. The report added that she had not received salary for the last three months and was even humiliated by her department. (PTI)                                                                                                                          
